>fucking paid 25$ for a 38yr old cd.
I've been picking up the originals of CD and cassette for more years than I want to count. Funny what you can find if you befriend the old guys. But I'm not selling any of my 80s thrash/death/black stuff.
Had on Countdown to Extinction the other week, and while the improved production & playing to a solid click track did Dave well, his free-wheeling coke-up days were a beast. It's all a matter of what you want right then; I love the uncompromising groove Menza & Elfeson had on that disc.
As I've gotten older, I appreciate the power that decent production brings to metal. If you're familiar with how classical is recorded, there's a parallel; some people believe the only way to do it is two mics in a concert hall, and others want each instrument miced and sound baffles between the chairs.
If you've heard the power of something like Mozart's Requiem or Bach's Mass in B minor live, you understand. Humans are creatures of deep power. Anthros would revel in that ephemeral moment.
